a latex tutorial PDF, created using latex which contains “live code + output” demonstration.

=> Each example has separate `.tex` file inside an `example_codes/` directory.
=> Each chapter (`tables.tex`, `lists.tex`, etc.) includes these files twice:
    : Once using `\input{...}` → to render the actual LaTeX output.
    : Once using `\lstinputlisting{...}` → to display the source code verbatim.
=> The `\subfile` command is used to include chapter files(ex \subfile{chapters/chap02-tables/tables})
=> The `\subfix` command is used for correct relative paths (example \input{\subfix{example_codes/table_01_simple_example.tex}})
=> No float or minipage environments are used, since they can create awkward white spaces or split examples across pages.
=> Page control is done manually:
    : \newpage → Starts a new page.
    : \clearpage → Starts a new page and flushes pending floats, ensuring clean layout control.


